Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Security Onion services not starting

Solution: Check system resources (RAM, disk space)
Run: sudo so-status to identify failed services
Review logs: sudo tail -f /var/log/syslog
Issue: No logs appearing in Kibana

Solution: Verify Elasticsearch is running: sudo systemctl status elasticsearch
Check index patterns are correctly configured
Ensure network interface is properly monitored
Issue: Python scripts cannot read log files

Solution: Run scripts with sudo or adjust file permissions
Verify log file paths exist: ls -la /nsm/zeek/logs/current/
Check Security Onion log rotation settings
Conclusion
This lab provided hands-on experience with Security Onion's network security monitoring capabilities using Zeek and Suricata. You configured custom detection rules, analyzed network traffic logs, and developed automated anomaly detection systems. These skills are essential for security operations centers (SOCs) and network defense teams. Continue practicing by analyzing different traffic patterns and refining your detection rules based on emerging threats.
